  "doc_id": "27064",
  "text": "Once the search has ended, B-Course gives the final report together with a list of ways to study the selected dependency model (see Fig. 3 ). The final report displays the constructed graph structure which the user can save if needed. The user is also given a report on strengths of the pairwise unconditional dependencies (i.e., arcs in the constructed Bayesian network) of the model. In addition to the standard Bayesian network representation, B-Course also offers two graphical representations describing the possible causal relationships that may have caused the dependencies of the model. These causal graphs are based on the calculus introduced by Pearl [CITATION_1] . As far as we know this feature is unique to B-Course, we are not aware of any other software package supporting Pearl's causal analysis.",
